main event: A witness in Bethel, Alaska observed a silver, aircraft-like object with multiple flashing lights on January 29, 1962.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 25 to 30 feet in size and maneuvered like a craft, but emitted no sound and had no visible exhaust.
The object was first thought to be an interference or malfunction, but appeared to be operating under its own control.
The witness was a licensed private pilot for 15 years and considered very reliable.
No possible cause or identity other than the description in the report could be found.
The sighting lasted for about 5 minutes.
sighted object: a silver, aircraft-like object with multiple flashing lights
witnesses: a civilian witness, a licensed private pilot
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
